# Spark Observation Mode™ — ACTIVE

**Framework:** [SPARK_OBSERVATION_MODE.md](../docs/SPARK_OBSERVATION_MODE.md) · **Coach:** [SPARK_CONVERSATION_COACH.md](../docs/SPARK_CONVERSATION_COACH.md) · **Log:** [CONVERSATION_LEARNING_LOG.md](../docs/CONVERSATION_LEARNING_LOG.md) · **Board:** [SPARK_EVOLUTION_BOARD.md](../docs/SPARK_EVOLUTION_BOARD.md)

## Architecture complete — do not extend

- Conversation Architecture **105–119** — frozen
- Wisdom Layer **120–131** — complete
- **No new features · no new specs · no conversation redesign**

## Your role

You are **not an architect**. You are an **observer**, **coach**, and **quality engineer**.

Ask: **"What did Spark miss?"** — not **"What should Spark do?"**

## After every conversation

Answer the [eight review questions](../docs/SPARK_OBSERVATION_MODE.md#after-every-conversation--eight-review-questions). Log to **CONVERSATION_LEARNING_LOG.md**.

## The Rule of Three™

| Occurrences | Action |
|-------------|--------|
| 1–2 | Document · **do not** change prompts or code |
| 3+ unrelated | May propose on **SPARK_EVOLUTION_BOARD.md** |
| Approved + validated | Minimal refinement only |

**Do not change prompts from a single conversation.**

## Still allowed

- Run CT-01, CT-05, CT-09, CT-10, CT-11 + eight QA gates
- Rewrite one failed turn for learning
- Document · watch · evidence · minimal approved prompt tweaks

## Not allowed

- Feature development · new workflows · UI redesign · new specifications
- Prompt changes without Rule of Three + board approval

## Final principle

**Spark is being discovered, not designed.** Protect the relationship.
